content:
Insurance provides a streamlined quoting process for proposed prices of insurance products and services, for either a new opportunity or an existing customer.

During the quoting process, you collect information about requirements, configure coverages, price the plan, and then create a quote. The first part of the OmniScript configuration in the quote flow process is user input. This is where you gather up top-level information for the quote.

The first part of the OmniScript structure, Script Configuration, is where you get the whole quote ball rolling. This is a good spot to enter an account ID, an opportunity ID, or some kind of Salesforce Record ID, which identifies that piece of information for the OmniScript.

The user input part of the OmniScript configuration also includes more specific input fields such as insured items and product configurations. The InsQuoteService:createUpdateQuote service takes all your data seeding and other inputs, mashes it all up with the product ratings you called out, and provides a dollar figure output for plans and products.

There are different types of quoting processes including small group quoting, large group quoting, census management for quoting, employer contributions, using a price book, and more.
title: Streamlining Insurance Quoting Process
